<section class="blk blk--first">
  <p class="eyebrow">The Assembly</p>
  <h1>The Assembly</h1>
  <p class="lead">A real say — advisory first, honest about the limits.</p>
  <p>The Assembly is how Uncost stays accountable to the people who support it: propose ideas, prioritize work, raise objections, and vote on priorities — with every proposal, method, and aggregate outcome recorded publicly.</p>
</section>

<section class="blk blk--cream2">
  <p class="eyebrow">Status</p>
  <h2 class="sec">Not yet operational.</h2>
  <p><span class="status status--planned">Advisory at launch</span></p>
  <p>At launch, every Assembly outcome is advisory. No formal vote runs until the governance policy completes independent review, founder review, and legal and fiscal-sponsor review where applicable, and is formally adopted.</p>
  {{ gap("assembly-status-governance", "the specific governance-policy identifier and its review-and-adoption chain are design-authored and the policy id (POL-006) is uncited; author from the adopted governance policy before it ships") }}
</section>

<section class="blk">
  <p class="eyebrow">What supporters can do</p>
  <h2 class="sec">The participation loop.</h2>
  <p class="lead">Uncost gives supporters a structured, recorded voice — through proposals, surveys, prioritization, and eventually formal votes where law and governance permit.</p>
  {{ gap("assembly-participation-loop", "the four-step propose / deliberate / advise / see-the-record breakdown is a design-authored elaboration, and the proposal mechanics (public ASM reference, classification, conflict screen) are uncited; author from the governance policy before it ships") }}
</section>

<section class="blk blk--cream2">
  <p class="eyebrow">Standing rules</p>
  <h2 class="sec">Rules that don't bend.</h2>
  {{ gap("assembly-standing-rules", "the standing rules (one person one vote, no paid influence, private ballots / public records, Pledge-based eligibility) are design-authored and the eligibility mechanic is uncited; author from the governance policy before it ships") }}
  <p>No tokens, no on-chain voting, no crypto mechanics. The Assembly's value is trust and participation, not speculation.</p>
</section>

<section class="blk">
  <p class="eyebrow">The boundary</p>
  <h2 class="sec">The honest boundary.</h2>
  <p class="lead">What the Assembly can — and cannot — decide.</p>
  <h3>Advisory at launch</h3>
  <p>Every Assembly outcome starts advisory. Where law and governance allow, outcomes may come to determine bounded community priorities — which regions or sectors to focus on next, which community projects to pursue, the direction of public communications — and any such vote is marked subject to legal and fiduciary approval.</p>
  <h3>Reserved matters</h3>
  <p>Finances above set thresholds and legal, fiduciary, safeguarding, privacy, employment, and regulatory duties remain with responsible leadership and the fiscal sponsor. Any binding authority would require legal structure that does not yet exist. Eligibility mechanics, quorum, appeals, and pauses are defined in the governance policy before the first vote.</p>
  {{ gap("assembly-governance-policy-link", "the export links a draft governance policy by an uncited identifier (POL-006) with no registered public route; wire the link only once the reviewed policy has a published location") }}
</section>

